Boil a half-full kettle.

Trim the @green beans{80%grams}. Cut into thirds.

Pour the boiling water into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Boil the @basmati rice{150%grams}, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain, pop back in the pan and cover.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Drain the @king prawns{225%grams}.

Once hot, fry the prawns and beans, ~{5-6%minutes}. 

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw prawns.

Next, add the @peri peri seasoning{1%sachet} and @tomato puree{30%grams} to the prawns. Stir-fry, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @vegetable stock paste{10%grams}, @smoky base paste{1%sachet}, @butter{20%grams}, @honey{1%tbsp} and @water for the sauce{100%ml}.

Bring to a boil. Simmer, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Cook so they're opaque in the middle of the prawns.

Add the rice to the prawns. Stir well to coat. Taste and season with @?salt and @?pepper if needed.

Share between your #bowls{}. Top with the @soured cream{75%grams}.

Enjoy!